<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Maximum_entropy_distributio=
n">Maximum entropy distribution</h3></div>
<p>Among all continuous probability distributions with <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Support_(mathematics)#In_probability_and_measure_theor=
y" title=3D"Support (mathematics)">support</a> <span class=3D"texhtml">[0, =
=E2=88=9E)</span> and mean <i>=CE=BC</i>, the exponential distribution with=
 <i>=CE=BB</i> =3D 1/<i>=CE=BC</i> has the largest <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Differential_entropy" title=3D"Differential entropy">diffe=
rential entropy</a>. In other words, it is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Maximum_entropy_probability_distribution" title=3D"Maximum ent=
ropy probability distribution">maximum entropy probability distribution</a>=
 for a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Random_variate" class=3D"mw=
-redirect" title=3D"Random variate">random variate</a> <i>X</i> which is gr=
eater than or equal to zero and for which E[<i>X</i>] is fixed.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exp=
onential_distribution#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
