<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Bayesian_inference_with_a_c=
alibrating_prior">Bayesian inference with a calibrating prior</h3></div>
<p>The exponential distribution is one of a number of statistical distribut=
ions with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_(mathematics)" tit=
le=3D"Group (mathematics)">group</a> structure. As a result of the group st=
ructure, the exponential has an associated <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Haar_measure" title=3D"Haar measure">Haar measure</a>, which is <s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-m=
ath-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmln=
s=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 1/\lambd=
a .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>=CE=BB<!-- =CE=BB --></mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 1/\lambda .}<=
/annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8732f4dee0b6b7bd07b06c1de87504e5b4ecf23b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:4.327ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 1/\=
lambda .}"></span>The use of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H=
aar_measure" title=3D"Haar measure">Haar measure</a> as the <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prior_probability" title=3D"Prior probability">pr=
ior</a> (known as the Haar prior) in a Bayesian prediction gives probabilit=
ies that are perfectly calibrated, for any underlying true parameter values=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Exponential_distribution#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expo=
