r" title=3D"Jeffreys prior">Jeffreys prior</a> 1/<i>=CE=BB,</i> which is eq=
ual to the right Haar prior in this case. Predictions generated using the r=
ight Haar prior are guaranteed to give perfectly calibrated probabilities.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-21" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
