<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Random_variate_generation">=
Random variate generation</h2></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Further information: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-uniform_r=
andom_variate_generation" title=3D"Non-uniform random variate generation">N=
on-uniform random variate generation</a></div>
<p>A conceptually very simple method for generating exponential <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variate" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Varia=
te">variates</a> is based on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inver=
se_transform_sampling" title=3D"Inverse transform sampling">inverse transfo=
rm sampling</a>: Given a random variate <i>U</i> drawn from the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_distribution_(continuous)" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Uniform distribution (continuous)">uniform distributio=
n</a> on the unit interval <span class=3D"texhtml">(0, 1)</span>, the varia=
te
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle T=3DF^{-1}(U)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>F</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>U</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T=3DF^{-1}(U)=
}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
