^{-1}(p)=3D{\frac {-\ln(1-p)}{\lambda }}.}"></span>
</p><p>Moreover, if <i>U</i> is uniform on (0, 1), then so is 1 =E2=88=92 <=
i>U</i>.  This means one can generate exponential variates as follows:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
